to practice full deployment and configuration every time. This hands-on repetition ensures I can rebuild 
from scratch on demand‚Äîjust like a real cloud admin‚Äîand helps me deeply retain each step of the Azure workflow.]

- This time, I set up VM backups and Recovery Services Vaults with a cleaner, more organized approach.
- Enabled and tested Azure Backup for a Linux VM, using cost-saving storage and policies.
- Successfully restored a VM from backup, troubleshooting every step for deeper understanding (NSG, public IP, password resets).
- Reinforced and deepened my Azure admin skills, now I am way more confident and efficient than before.
- Set up soft delete for blobs and containers, adding an easy recovery layer for accidental deletes.
- Now I understand how retention periods (ex: 7 days) give a real safety net before permanent deletion.
- The soft delete feature is simple to enable, and adds confidence for handling production data.
- Reinforces the habit of thinking about data protection and disaster recovery early in any setup.
- Each time I build these settings from scratch, I get faster and more comfortable with Azure‚Äôs storage features.
